00E13A  2               ; character get subroutine for zero page
00E13A  2               
00E13A  2               ; For a 1.8432MHz 6502 including the JSR and RTS
00E13A  2               ; fastest (>=":") =  29 cycles =  15.7uS
00E13A  2               ; slowest (<":")  =  40 cycles =  21.7uS
00E13A  2               ; space skip      = +21 cycles = +11.4uS
00E13A  2               ; inc across page =  +4 cycles =  +2.2uS
00E13A  2               
00E13A  2               ; the target address for the LDA at LAB_2CF4 becomes the BASIC execute pointer once the
00E13A  2               ; block is copied to it's destination, any non zero page address will do at assembly
00E13A  2               ; time, to assemble a three byte instruction.
00E13A  2               
